3. Design a contact us form with all fields as required.

---
<html lang="en">
   <head>
       <title>Contact Us
       </title>
   <style>
       h1 {text-align: center;}
   </style>
   </head>
   <body>
   <div>
       <h1> Contact Us</h1><br>
       <form>
           <label for="Name"> First Name</label>
           <input type="Name" id="Name" value="Name" placeholder="Enter your Name"/> <br> <br>
           <label for="Phone"> Phone Number</label>
           <input type="tel" id="Phone" value="Phone" placeholder="Enter your Phone number"/><br> <br>
           <label for="email">Email Address</label>
           <input type="email" id="Email" value="Email" placeholder="Enter your email id"/> <br> <br>
           <label for="Country">Select Country</label>
<select name="Country" id="Country">
   <option value="India">India</option>
   <option value="Australia">Australia</option>
   <option value="Germany">Germany</option>
   <option value="Asia">Asia</option>
   <option value="Africa">Africa</option>
</select> <br> <br>
 
<input type="submit"/>
       </form>
      
           </div>
       </body>
   </html>

4. Use certain HTML elements to display the following in a HTML page.


Programming Language
JavaScript
Angular
React
Vue.js
Python
Django Framework
Flask Framework
Java
Spring
Maven
Hibernate
Database
MySQL
MongoDB
Cansandra

—
<html lang="en">
   <head>
       <title>Bullet Sample
       </title>
       <style>
  .circle
  {
list-style-type: circle;
  }
  .disc{
list-style-type: disc;
  }
  .lower-alpha{
list-style-type: lower-alpha;
  }
       </style>
   </head>
   <body>
   <ul class="disc">
       <li>Programming Language</li>
   <ul class="circle">
       <li> JavaScript</li>
       <ul class="lower-alpha">
           <li>Angular</li>
           <li>React</li>
           <li>Vue</li>
       </ul>
       </ul>
   <ul class="circle">
       <li>Python</li>
       <ul class="lower-alpha">
           <li>Django Framework</li>
           <li>Flask Framework</li>
           </ul>
   </ul>
   <ul class="circle">
       <li>Java</li>
       <ul class="lower-alpha">
           <li>Spring</li>
           <li>Maven</li>
           <li>Hibernate</li>
           </ul>
   </ul>
   </ul>
   <ul class="disc">
       <li>Database</li>
       <ul class="circle">
           <li>MYSQL</li>
           <li>MongoDB</li>
           <li>Cassandra</li>
       </body>
   </html>


5. Create an element that helps you to open the https://google.com in separate new tab.

—
<html lang="en">
   <head>
       <title>Hyperlink Sample
       </title>
   </head>
   <body>
       <a href="https://google.com">Visit google</a>
       </body>
   </html>


6. In the form, add two radio buttons with grouping them for employee type(Salaried and own business)

—
<html lang="en">
   <head>
       <title>Radiobutton Sample
       </title>
   </head>
   <body>
       <form>
           <p>Employee Type</p><br>
           <input type="radio" id="html" name="employee_type" value="HTML"/>
           <label for="html">Salaried</label><br>
           <input type="radio" id="html" name="employee_type" value="HTML"/>
           <label for="html">Own Business</label><br>
           <input type="Submit"/>
       </form>
       </body>
   </html>


